components.name: Fetch AirVisual Data
components.description: Fetches current air quality and weather data from the AirVisual API, performs duplicate detection, and saves the data as a JSON file.

components.name: Read and Validate AirVisual Data
components.description: Reads the JSON file created by the previous task and validates the data integrity before loading into the database.

upstream_policy.description: Depends on successful completion of get_airvisual_data_hourly.

components.name: Load AirVisual Data to PostgreSQL
components.description: Transforms the validated JSON data into a dimensional model and loads it into PostgreSQL tables with proper referential integrity.
outputs: Records in dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable

upstream_policy.description: Depends on successful completion of read_data_airvisual.

name.constraints: Must be a unique identifier for the pipeline

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

LATITUDE.constraints: Must be a valid latitude coordinate

LONGITUDE.constraints: Must be a valid longitude coordinate

file_path.description: Path to the JSON file created by the previous task
file_path.constraints: Must be a valid file path

mapping_main_pollution_file.description: Path to the main pollution mapping file
mapping_main_pollution_file.constraints: Must be a valid file path

mapping_weather_code_file.description: Path to the weather code mapping file
mapping_weather_code_file.constraints: Must be a valid file path

sources: AirVisual API (http://api.airvisual.com/v2/nearest_city) - Fetches current air quality and weather data using latitude/longitude coordinates.
sinks: PostgreSQL Database (airvisual_db) - Stores the transformed data in dimensional tables (dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable).
